The purpose of the SPCC document is to also establish procedures to notify appropriate agencies (like the LEPC and the fire department) and company personnel in the event of an emergency.  It includes planning for potential spills and the appropriate responses and countermeasures.



Our comprehensive emergency response plan is designed to protect our employees and the community and, among other things, requires that:

     - All non-essential personnel immediately exit the area affected by the spill;

     - Kraft Heinz immediately notify local officials, requesting their assistance, if necessary;



For a release that leaves the site, the company would work with the local fire and police officials to notify neighbors so that appropriate safety precautions could be taken.  If ammonia is in the outside atmosphere, the safest place to be is indoors with the windows and doors shut.
